Scully.io is a great tool for Angular developers. Its tagline is, “Scully makes building, testing and deploying JAMstack apps extremely simple.” Essentially, you build your application in Angular and then Scully will take it and generate static HTML and CSS for you. Those assets can be deployed, and the end result is a high quality, blazing fast experience. In this post, we’ll talk about how you can extend the default functionality of Scully to better suit your need…

Getting started


To get started, you'll need the Serverless Framework installed. You'll also need your environment configured with AWS credentials. 
Then, let's install a few dependencies. We'll install the express framework, as well as the serverless-http:
$ npm install --save express serverless-http 

Then create a file index.js and initialize it like so:
const serverless = require('serverless-http');
const express = require('express')
const app = express()

